  "prompt": "How do l see who viewed my videos on Instagram?",
  "response": "As of now, **Instagram does not provide a feature** that allows you to see who viewed your **regular videos** (posts, Stories, or Reels). However, there are some specific cases where you can see viewer information:\n\n### 1. **Instagram Stories**\n   - For **Stories**, you can see a list of people who viewed your video by swiping up on your Story (if your account is public or private and you have followers).\n   - The list shows usernames and the number of views.\n\n### 2. **Instagram Live Videos**\n   - If you go **Live**, you can see the usernames of viewers who joined your Live in real-time.\n   - After the Live ends, you can also view the number of viewers and the usernames of some participants.\n\n### 3. **Instagram Reels**\n   - For **Reels**, you can see the **total number of views** but not the specific usernames of who viewed them.\n\n### 4. **Instagram Posts (Regular Videos)**\n   - For **regular video posts**, you can only see the **total number of views** and the usernames of people who liked or commented on the post.\n\n### Notes:\n- Be cautious of third-party apps or websites claiming to show you who viewed your Instagram videos. These are often scams, violate Instagram's terms of service, and can compromise your account security.\n- Instagram may update its features in the future, so it's a good idea to stay updated with the app's official announcements.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
